    {
      "paragraph_name": "REPOSITION-AUTHORIZATIONS",
      "summary": null,
      "purpose": "This paragraph repositions the IMS database cursor to a specific authorization key. It moves WS-AUTH-KEY-SAVE to PA-AUTHORIZATION-KEY and then retrieves the PAUTDTL1 segment using DLI GNP with a WHERE clause to match the authorization key. It moves the DIBSTAT to IMS-RETURN-CODE and evaluates the status. If the status is OK, it sets AUTHS-NOT-EOF to TRUE. If the segment is not found or end of database is reached, it sets AUTHS-EOF to TRUE. If any other error occurs, it sets WS-ERR-FLG to 'Y', constructs an error message, and calls SEND-PAULST-SCREEN to display the error.",
