    {
      "paragraph_name": "RECEIVE-PAULST-SCREEN",
      "summary": null,
      "purpose": "This paragraph receives data from the COPAU0A screen. It executes a CICS RECEIVE command to receive the data from the screen into the COPAU0AI map. The RESP and RESP2 options capture the CICS response codes in WS-RESP-CD and WS-REAS-CD, respectively. The paragraph consumes data from the COPAU0A screen and populates the COPAU0AI map. It does not call any other paragraphs or programs. The CICS RECEIVE command handles potential errors, with the response codes stored in WS-RESP-CD and WS-REAS-CD.",
