    {
      "paragraph_name": "SCHEDULE-PSB",
      "summary": null,
      "purpose": "The SCHEDULE-PSB paragraph is responsible for scheduling a Program Specification Block (PSB) for IMS database interaction. It first attempts to schedule the PSB using the EXEC DLI SCHD command, specifying the PSB name and disabling the Dhabend exit. The DIBSTAT field is then moved to IMS-RETURN-CODE to capture the IMS return code. If the PSB has been scheduled more than once, it terminates the current PSB and reschedules it. If the scheduling is successful (STATUS-OK), it sets the IMS-PSB-SCHD flag to TRUE. Otherwise, it sets the WS-ERR-FLG to 'Y', constructs an error message including the IMS return code, sets ACCTIDL to -1, and performs the SEND-PAULST-SCREEN paragraph to display the error message to the user. This paragraph ensures the program connects to the IMS database and handles potential scheduling errors.",
